<br>
If you blind the mob you and your warder are fighting under normal circumstances and back up, it will do like normal blinded mobs and keep fighting the thing closest to it, your warder, instead of fleeing.<br>
<br>
However, if you have LHA (low health aggro), the mob WILL flee and ignore the pet, because, I am assuming, LHA tells it to REALLY hate you and ignore the warder, but since it can't get at you, it's like the warder is not there.<br>
<br>
What this means, at least in practice, is that if I know I am LHA, I can aggro kite, just by landing a blind and backing up. The mob flees, the pet nips at him, and he turns back towards me every now and then, but generally flees and ignores the pet until the blind wears off, behaving as if he had been feared.<br>
<br>
Just noting my observations. <p><center>
